sql:
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM case_data) AS total_cases,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users) AS total_users;

SELECT HEX(nuts_id) AS hexadecimal_code
FROM nuts_regions
WHERE country_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- A 'NUTS region' refers to a Nomenclature of Territorial Units for Statistics region; 
- A 'case' may refer to an instance of a disease being tracked; 
- The query assumes that the 'top region' is the one with the highest total case count; 
- The query retrieves all available case data for the top region, including the number of cases, lower and upper bounds of cases, date and time of the report, type of disease, source of the data, and any additional notes.
